0.037     2026-06-22
          - New: optional, LOCAL semantic search -- `pcg search --semantic <intent>` /
            pcg_search semantic:true ranks symbols by MEANING (embedding cosine similarity),
            for when you know what code should do but not what it is called ("where do we
            validate user input"). NO cloud dependency: a local provider via PCG_EMBED_CMD (any
            command emitting one JSON float-array per input line) or an Ollama-compatible
            endpoint (PCG_EMBED_URL / PCG_EMBED_MODEL). `pcg index --embed` (pcg_index
            embed:true) embeds every named symbol from its qualified-name + signature +
            docstring into a new `embeddings` table; the query is embedded at search time and
            ranked by dot product (vectors stored L2-normalized, so cosine == dot). Degrades
            gracefully -- no provider -> --embed is skipped with a note and --semantic returns
            guidance, so keyword `pcg search` always works. Embeddings persist by stable node
            id and stale ones (deleted symbols) are pruned on re-embed. New App::PerlGraph::
            Embed; Schema embeddings table; Store upsert/all/count/prune; Query::semantic;
            Format::semantic; CLI `search --semantic` + `index --embed`.
          - Tests +10 (1037 total): t/80 drives the whole pipeline with a deterministic fake
