0.035     2026-06-22
          - Interprocedural type inference: `my $x = foo(); $x->method` now resolves when
            foo() has an inferred return type (a `Class->new` builder). The extractor already
            inferred a sub's return type (metadata.returns) and used it for chained
            `func()->m`, but an assignment-from-call did not propagate that type to the
            variable -- so $x->method stayed opaque. Now `my $x = foo()` records a deferred
            "return-of-foo" type and the resolver resolves foo + reads its returns to type $x
            (provenance `inferred`; never fabricates a method the class lacks). Shrinks the
            opaque-dispatch frontier one hop further, across a call boundary. New
            Extractor::_call_name + the receiver_call candidate; Resolver receiver_call path.
            EXTRACTION_VERSION 4->5.
          - Tests +2 (1026 total): t/59 (interprocedural resolve + that it picks the producer
            return type over a globally-ambiguous same-named method).

