0.029     2026-06-21
          - Pre-release review (multi-agent, several passes over the whole dist). Fixes:
            * CORRECTNESS (pcg diff / review on non-ASCII code): the working-tree side read
              the file with slurp_utf8 (decoded characters) while the git side (git show)
              and every other parse site use raw bytes -- so a sub whose name contains
              non-ASCII (or any unicode identifier) keyed differently on each side and an
              UNCHANGED such sub was reported as both removed AND added (a phantom breaking
              change). Diff now reads raw bytes, matching git show. (t/70)
            * CORRECTNESS (pcg lsp): a well-framed but MALFORMED JSON message body killed
              the server -- the decode failure returned undef, which the read loop treats as
              EOF, so one bad frame ended the session. A malformed frame is now skipped (the
              server keeps serving); only a true EOF stops it. (t/63)
            * ROBUSTNESS (pcg install / uninstall): a malformed ~/.claude.json or
              ~/.claude/settings.json crashed the command with a raw JSON exception;
              _read_json now reports a clear "cannot parse FILE" error and leaves the file
              untouched (rather than risk clobbering it). (t/16)
            * ROBUSTNESS (parallel-indexer fork-safety): the child's extraction loop sat
              OUTSIDE its eval guard, so a worker that died mid-extract could unwind past
              the fork block and run on as a rogue process -- under the long-lived MCP
              server, a second server writing on the shared stdout. The whole child body
              is now eval-wrapped so any failure reaches POSIX::_exit; the parent already
              redoes a failed chunk serially. (t/42)
            * ROBUSTNESS (--runtime on a THREADED perl -- the common distro/macOS build):
              the optree enricher read a method_named op's name via meth_sv, which is a
              null B::SPECIAL on a threaded perl, so dynamic `$self->method` calls never
              resolved to authoritative `optree` edges (they stayed at the static
              `heuristic`). The name lives in the CV's pad at op->targ there; new
              Runtime::_meth_name reads it (mirrors the gv-in-pad _find_gv fix, but METHOP
              uses ->targ not ->padix). Caught by the threaded CI matrix entry running for
              the first time. (t/20, t/21)
            * Removed dead code: Store::file_hashes -- orphaned when _index_parallel
              switched to file_states in 0.027 (zero callers).
            * Docs synced: `pcg unresolved --by-receiver` added to bin/pcg POD + README
              (the README never listed `pcg unresolved` at all); a note that a pcg upgrade
              re-extracts unchanged files (extraction_version); the by_receiver workflow in
              the agent-mediated resolve section. A comprehensive audit of every MCP tool
              description against its actual output corrected three agent-facing inaccuracies:
              pcg_hotspots said "most complex (fan-out)" (it returns FOUR lists -- fan-in,
              fan-out, cyclomatic complexity, efferent coupling; the CLI/POD/README lines too);
              pcg_review claimed it "composes ... impact" (it composes the affected-file
              closure, not the impact query) and a caller count for "each touched symbol" (only
              breaking ones are shown); pcg_diff omitted `class` from its kind list. The other
              21 tool descriptions audited accurate.
            * `pcg unresolved --by-receiver --name M` (and the MCP by_receiver+name) now
              narrows to the receivers that call method M -- previously --name was silently
              ignored in by-receiver mode. Added `--by-receiver` to the SYNOPSIS too. The
              by-receiver list defaults to limit 50, matching plain `unresolved` and the
              documented pcg_unresolved default (was an undocumented 40).
            * Tests +28 (976 total): the regressions above (non-ASCII diff t/70, LSP
              malformed-frame t/63, malformed-config install t/16, parallel fork-fault t/42);
              new coverage for CLI
              happy-paths of the git commands risk / cochange / diff / review incl.
              risk --since (t/75, which previously covered only their no-git error paths),
              a fresh-home install (t/16), and `index --runtime` flag-through (t/58);
              extraction_version re-extract in the PARALLEL path (t/42), resolve_targets
              multi-class intersection + ranking + the --name filter (t/74), pcg_unresolved
              by_receiver via MCP + the status lib/test split (t/15), CLI `unresolved
