0.025     2026-06-21
          - LLM resolution at scale: pcg_resolve gains a receiver-TYPE form
            { caller, receiver, class } -- infer a receiver variable's class ONCE and
            every opaque method call on it in that caller resolves against the class's
            MRO at once (one entry handles $db->query, $db->fetch, ...), instead of a
            per-call { caller, method, receiver, target }. Both forms write `llm` edges,
            never fabricate a method the class lacks, and persist across reindex. Turns
            "resolve 25k calls" into "type a few thousand receivers" (on jakutia 87%% of
            the 29k opaque calls have a real candidate, 13.8k a unique one). New
            Resolver::method_in_mro. t/74 covers the type form, the no-fabrication
            guard, persistence, and the still-supported explicit form.

0.024     2026-06-21
          - Cross-distribution resolution: `pcg index --deps` (and pcg_index deps:true)
            also indexes the PUBLIC API of the CPAN modules the project use's /
            inherits from -- located in @INC WITHOUT running any code -- so calls into
            dependencies resolve. Foo->new->bar, a literal CPAN::Class->method, and
            inherited $self->method (up the MRO into an indexed parent like
            Mojolicious::Controller) all link to real nodes. CPAN nodes carry
            metadata.cpan and are excluded from unused/untested; only public subs +
            inheritance edges are kept (no internal call graph), crawled with a cap
            and fail-soft per module. On jakutia (a Mojo app): 223 deps indexed,
            ~1973 previously-opaque calls resolved.
